{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Syria has no &#8220;moderate opposition&#8221; to help us. But maybe Assad could.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by policy expert Ahmad Samih Khalidi warns plan to back Syrian opposition as part of campaign against the Islamic State in Iraq and Syria is deeply misguided; contends there is no true 'moderate opposition' in Syria or the Middle East, and that wisest plan would be to begin a political engagement with Bashar al-Assad, despite brutality of his regime; holds Assad's Syrian Army is one of the few regional forces capable of confronting ISIS on the ground.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "27", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"lastname": "KHALIDI", "rank": 1, "firstname": "Ahmad", "role": "reported", "organization": "", "middlename": "Samih"}], "original": "By AHMAD SAMIH KHALIDI", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/16/opinion/to-crush-isis-make-a-deal-with-assad-.html", "lead_paragraph": "Syria has no &#8220;moderate opposition&#8221; to help us. But maybe Assad could.", "headline": {"main": "To Crush ISIS, Make a Deal With Assad", "print_headline": "To Crush ISIS, Make a Deal With Assad", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor", "kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor"}, "_id": "5417796338f0d851fd3a802b", "word_count": "970", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/09/16/opinion/0916OPEDrota/0916OPEDrota-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/09/16/opinion/0916OPEDrota/0916OPEDrota-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 761, "url": "images/2014/09/16/opinion/0916OPEDrota/0916OPEDrota-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/09/16/opinion/0916OPEDrota/0916OPEDrota-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "761"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/09/16/opinion/0916OPEDrota/0916OPEDrota-thumbStandard.